text:
How could we turn our backs on such raw, awe-inspiring beauty? Why did we evolve to live in concrete jungles, trapped in the rat race of corporate life, surrounded by anxiety, toxicity, and pollutionüò©

Why have we evolved to chase artificial material gains? We will eventually die alone and this material pursuit will leave you questioning at your death bed. I feel that our truest, most profound happiness stems from immersing ourselves in nature. This sight of a raw rugged green mountain and crystal-clear lake opens my heart, sending waves of joy coursing through my entire being. 

Why have we retreated to cities? attempting to recreate pale imitations of nature's splendor in manicured parks and potted plants? 

I find myself yearning for a life that clubs together the simplicity and connection to nature of the 19th century with the technological advancement of our modern age.
